<i>Up next is a character who reminds us</i>

975
00:48:07.458 --> 00:48:10.540
<i>it's never too late to try something new.</i>

976
00:48:10.541 --> 00:48:11.832
<i>Leo has spent years…</i>

977
00:48:11.833 --> 00:48:15.833
I almost had to beat up an old
lady to get these tiny marshmallows.

978
00:48:16.333 --> 00:48:18.166
But I got 'em! Ha-ha-ha!

979
00:48:19.291 --> 00:48:22.332
<i>Oh. Leo. Truly inspiring.</i>

980
00:48:22.333 --> 00:48:25.625
<i>and he brings back happy memories for me…</i>

981
00:48:26.125 --> 00:48:29.165
Hey. D? You ask your mom if she needs any help?

982
00:48:29.166 --> 00:48:30.707
I'm doing the mashed potatoes!

983
00:48:30.708 --> 00:48:33.915
Okay. well. that's the easiest one.
Can you see if she needs anything?

984
00:48:33.916 --> 00:48:36.540
- Jesus!
- Make yourself available.

985
00:48:36.541 --> 00:48:39.290
- Fine.
- Mick Jagger with the sunglasses.

986
00:48:39.291 --> 00:48:42.291
- Celeste. you can sit.
- Oh. no. I insist.

987
00:48:42.791 --> 00:48:44.541
Okay. fine. Love you. Brian.

988
00:48:49.666 --> 00:48:51.291
Babe. did you get the carrots?

989
00:48:52.416 --> 00:48:54.624
<i>I am annoying. I am fake.</i>

990
00:48:54.625 --> 00:48:56.665
<i>I'm not who I'm being. I'm pretending…</i>

991
00:48:56.666 --> 00:48:58.166
Have you ever seen <i>Drag Race?</i>

992
00:48:58.666 --> 00:49:00.207
Uh… no.

993
00:49:00.208 --> 00:49:02.583
<i>How am I supposed to feel in this moment…</i>

994
00:49:03.083 --> 00:49:05.749
You should. You'd love it.

995
00:49:05.750 --> 00:49:08.290
<i>I didn't wanna make it that everybody was attacking you!</i>

996
00:49:08.291 --> 00:49:10.041
<i>I feel very attacked!</i>

997
00:49:11.500 --> 00:49:12.625
Ugh.

998
00:49:14.250 --> 00:49:16.833
Celeste seems like a good hang.
Did you have fun last night?

999
00:49:17.333 --> 00:49:19.540
Uh. yeah. unfortunately.

1000
00:49:19.541 --> 00:49:21.499
When I was in college and had a hangover.

1001
00:49:21.500 --> 00:49:24.499
I'd drink a whole bottle of wine. eat some chicken nuggets.

1002
00:49:24.500 --> 00:49:26.374
take a nap. and just sleep all day.

1003
00:49:26.375 --> 00:49:28.415
Mom. that's really sad.

1004
00:49:28.416 --> 00:49:31.333
Well. all moms are a little sad. You'll see.

1005
00:49:32.416 --> 00:49:35.874
Hello. Weisz family!

1006
00:49:35.875 --> 00:49:38.624
- Happy Thanksgiving! We're here!
- Hi. babies!

1007
00:49:38.625 --> 00:49:39.540
- Hi.
- Hi. Mom.

1008
00:49:39.541 --> 00:49:41.207
- Happy Thanksgiving!
- Hi!

1009
00:49:41.208 --> 00:49:43.582
- I… I brought the Negronis.
- Hi.

1010
00:49:43.583 --> 00:49:45.332
- Hi.
- It's so good to see you.

1011
00:49:45.333 --> 00:49:48.249
- Happy Thanksgiving. Gigi.
- Happy Thanksgiving. my dear.

1012
00:49:48.250 --> 00:49:51.249
Honey. how is college going?

1013
00:49:51.250 --> 00:49:53.290
Are you an architect yet?

1014
00:49:53.291 --> 00:49:54.665
Ha! No. not yet.

1015
00:49:54.666 --> 00:49:58.499
Well. did you tell those professors
about the house that I live in?

1016
00:49:58.500 --> 00:50:01.708
- Yeah. I did.
- That didn't buy you… Uh-oh.

1017
00:50:02.291 --> 00:50:04.749
Who is this beautiful young woman?

1018
00:50:04.750 --> 00:50:07.040
Oh. this is… this is my roommate. Celeste.

1019
00:50:07.041 --> 00:50:08.915
Celeste?

1020
00:50:08.916 --> 00:50:11.582
Well. I am your Gigi.

1021
00:50:11.583 --> 00:50:13.624
Now come here. come here.

1022
00:50:13.625 --> 00:50:15.041
Mwah!

1023
00:50:15.541 --> 00:50:19.249
Here's Brian! Hi!

1024
00:50:19.250 --> 00:50:21.332
Bulla. you grew your mustache back.

1025
00:50:21.333 --> 00:50:23.957
- Just to piss you off.
- Mission accomplished.

1026
00:50:23.958 --> 00:50:26.124
D. can you help me with the turkey. please?

1027
00:50:26.125 --> 00:50:28.365
- Want me to get Alex?
- No. I don't trust him near this.

1028
00:50:29.166 --> 00:50:31.540
- You are a wanted woman.
- I'll start the sprouts.

1029
00:50:31.541 --> 00:50:32.457
Thank you. honey.

1030
00:50:32.458 --> 00:50:34.500
- Hi. Mom.
- Come on. I need my girl.

1031
00:50:35.583 --> 00:50:38.290
Why don't you get it?

1032
00:50:38.291 --> 00:50:40.249
- I need some ice.
- You got it.

1033
00:50:40.250 --> 00:50:41.582
Can I get you a drink?

1034
00:50:41.583 --> 00:50:42.833
- Yes.
- Come on.

1035
00:50:43.333 --> 00:50:47.582
Ooh! Hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

1036
00:50:47.583 --> 00:50:49.249
It's good. You can do kettle bell.

1037
00:50:49.250 --> 00:50:51.625
You can kinda do your kettle bell exercise like that.

1038
00:50:52.208 --> 00:50:53.875
You can swing it. too. if you want.

1039
00:50:55.500 --> 00:50:58.165
I don't want this to look sexual. I'm doing it wrong.

1040
00:50:58.166 --> 00:50:59.874
- It is.
- Okay. then I'm gonna stop.

1041
00:50:59.875 --> 00:51:01.291
Can you take a picture?

1042
00:51:01.958 --> 00:51:03.125
Yeah.

1043
00:51:05.000 --> 00:51:06.582
- That's good.
- For the grid?

1044
00:51:06.583 --> 00:51:09.707
- No.
- Just for stories? Okay.

1045
00:51:09.708 --> 00:51:11.374
I'm gonna lower it down.

1046
00:51:11.375 --> 00:51:14.708
Ooh! Listen to that sizzle.

1047
00:51:15.666 --> 00:51:17.583
Celeste is. uh… She's funny.

1048
00:51:18.750 --> 00:51:20.708
- Yeah.
- You're funnier though.

1049
00:51:21.208 --> 00:51:23.833
- Thank you.
- Okay. Keep an eye on it. okay?

1050
00:51:24.333 --> 00:51:26.166
- Hey. D?
- Mm-hmm.

1051
00:51:26.791 --> 00:51:28.791
- I love you.
- I love you.

1052
00:51:33.583 --> 00:51:35.665
You are so cute!

1053
00:51:35.666 --> 00:51:37.750
- You are so cute!
- Oh my God.

1054
00:51:39.458 --> 00:51:41.125
Wow. no way!

1055
00:51:41.958 --> 00:51:43.875
Another one?

1056
00:51:49.916 --> 00:51:52.332
Hey. honey.

1057
00:51:52.333 --> 00:51:53.332
Hi.

1058
00:51:53.333 --> 00:51:55.458
- You're out here all alone?
- Yeah.

1059
00:51:56.083 --> 00:51:57.208
Now you're not.

1060
00:51:58.291 --> 00:52:01.291
You know. your friend in there is so pretty.

1061
00:52:02.250 --> 00:52:05.665
But those tattoos are so ugly.

1062
00:52:05.666 --> 00:52:08.665
- What is that about?
- Stop. Don't say that.

1063
00:52:08.666 --> 00:52:11.290
I'm gonna take a shift.

1064
00:52:11.291 --> 00:52:13.749
No. no. Go back inside. I got it.

1065
00:52:13.750 --> 00:52:17.124
They won't let me do anything in there.
I can watch a turkey.

1066
00:52:17.125 --> 00:52:20.791
Be with your friend. You brought her. Go be with her.

1067
00:52:22.500 --> 00:52:23.707
'Kay.

1068
00:52:23.708 --> 00:52:25.250
- Okay.
- Bye.

1069
00:52:30.166 --> 00:52:34.832
When I was your age. I got
a tattoo with my college boyfriend. Vern.

1070
00:52:34.833 --> 00:52:37.290
Oh my God. Vicki. you were crazy about Vern.

1071
00:52:37.291 --> 00:52:40.124
She was obsessed with Vern.
I mean. in fairness. everybody was.

1072
00:52:40.125 --> 00:52:42.916
I'll never forget how happy he made me.

1073
00:52:43.833 --> 00:52:46.665
Fun fact about Vern. he's now married to Whitney Cummings.

1074
00:52:46.666 --> 00:52:47.874
- Get out.
- Who?

1075
00:52:47.875 --> 00:52:52.040
Yeah. I know I act like I'm cool
with all the Vern talk. but I'm not.

1076
00:52:52.041 --> 00:52:54.790
Okay. you know Devon has a Vern.

1077
00:52:54.791 --> 00:52:55.957
He's her TA.

1078
00:52:55.958 --> 00:52:58.749
- What are you talking about?
- Really?

1079
00:52:58.750 --> 00:53:00.332
My Devon likes a boy.

1080
00:53:00.333 --> 00:53:03.124
Every time Devon's around him.

1081
00:53:03.125 --> 00:53:07.249
she's like. "Michael. I'm in love with you."

1082
00:53:07.250 --> 00:53:08.499
I don't say that.

1083
00:53:08.500 --> 00:53:11.000
- Something is going on out there.
- What?

1084
00:53:12.166 --> 00:53:13.415
Oh my God!

1085
00:53:13.416 --> 00:53:15.415
Oh. Mom! Mom!

1086
00:53:15.416 --> 00:53:16.999
Devon. go help!

1087
00:53:17.000 --> 00:53:19.124
Go! Mom! Mom!

1088
00:53:19.125 --> 00:53:20.999
Oh God. what do we do?

1089
00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:23.374
- Gigi's on fire!
- Oh my God! Ah!

1090
00:53:23.375 --> 00:53:24.416
I got it.

1091
00:53:28.625 --> 00:53:30.707
Oh my God! Mom. are you okay?

1092
00:53:30.708 --> 00:53:32.916
Mommy. Mommy… Oh my God.

1093
00:53:33.708 --> 00:53:34.708
What happened?

1094
00:53:35.333 --> 00:53:37.499
- I spilled my drink.
- You don't need that.

1095
00:53:37.500 --> 00:53:39.332
You all right? You okay?

1096
00:53:39.333 --> 00:53:41.166
- I'm okay.
- Okay. okay.

1097
00:53:42.708 --> 00:53:45.957
- You're supposed to be watching the fryer.
- She told me to go inside!

1098
00:53:45.958 --> 00:53:47.749
- I don't know!
- Brian. Brian. it's okay.

1099
00:53:47.750 --> 00:53:50.875
I knew Devon was out of it today.
so I had to be the responsible one.

1100
00:53:51.458 --> 00:53:55.749
Oh. what size head do you have?
I'm gonna crochet you a hat.

1101
00:53:55.750 --> 00:53:57.332
Grandma's hats are iconic.

1102
00:53:57.333 --> 00:54:00.832
- Celeste. that was unbelievable.
- An angel.

1103
00:54:00.833 --> 00:54:02.875
She was like a frickin' firefighter.

1104
00:54:06.708 --> 00:54:10.124
<i>Devon woke up the next morning with a stomach ache.</i>

1105
00:54:10.125 --> 00:54:13.708
<i>knowing she had to spend
the rest of the weekend with Celeste.</i>

1106
00:54:22.625 --> 00:54:24.832
<i>Immediately. she felt better.</i>

1107
00:54:24.833 --> 00:54:27.665
Hey. D. you up yet? Come have some breakfast.

1108
00:54:27.666 --> 00:54:29.124
I'm making waffles!

1109
00:54:29.125 --> 00:54:31.666
- Don't burn 'em. Dad!
- Too late!

1110
00:54:33.666 --> 00:54:37.958
<i>Devon returned to the dorms
just in time for her 19th birthday.</i>

1111
00:54:53.583 --> 00:54:56.250
- Happy birthday!
- God.

1112
00:54:57.750 --> 00:54:59.874
Thank you so much. This is so nice.

1113
00:54:59.875 --> 00:55:01.624
Of course. You like it?

1114
00:55:01.625 --> 00:55:03.499
Yeah. I can't believe you did all this.

1115
00:55:03.500 --> 00:55:07.665
So I'm thinking. for your birthday.
the four of us. we go to Abba.

1116
00:55:07.666 --> 00:55:10.749
It's. like. Mediterranean.
but they also have a hookah lounge.

1117
00:55:10.750 --> 00:55:12.874
- That sounds awesome.
- Nice. Okay.

1118
00:55:12.875 --> 00:55:14.666
- I'm gonna shower.
- Yeah.

1119
00:55:18.208 --> 00:55:19.208
Um…

1120
00:55:20.041 --> 00:55:22.082
Is that my bra and underwear?

1121
00:55:22.083 --> 00:55:24.791
Yeah. they were… in my drawer?

1122
00:55:44.000 --> 00:55:48.124
<i>Celeste's actions had moved
Devon from anxious to full-blown paranoid.</i>

1123
00:55:48.125 --> 00:55:49.707
<i>She needed a second opinion.</i>

1124
00:55:49.708 --> 00:55:52.625
<i>so she went to the smartest woman on campus.</i>

1125
00:55:53.750 --> 00:55:55.082
Hey. girly pop.

1126
00:55:55.083 --> 00:55:57.332
<i>Wait. you're in this story?</i>

1127
00:55:57.333 --> 00:55:59.374
Why do you have a fuckin' bowl cut?

1128
00:55:59.375 --> 00:56:00.832
It was a bob.

1129
00:56:00.833 --> 00:56:03.416
and how are you seeing that. anyway? That's weird.

1130
00:56:04.375 --> 00:56:06.957
Wow. These are awesome.

1131
00:56:06.958 --> 00:56:10.124
- My mom's a ceramicist.
- Oh. nice. Yeah.

1132
00:56:10.125 --> 00:56:12.707
The welding studio is. like. a 20-minute walk away.

1133
00:56:12.708 --> 00:56:15.290
so I was like. "Fuck walking."

1134
00:56:15.291 --> 00:56:16.625
Is the school okay with that?

1135
00:56:17.125 --> 00:56:18.166
No.

1136
00:56:20.083 --> 00:56:24.250
So you're just here to admire my decor.

1137
00:56:25.458 --> 00:56:28.500
I was wondering what the process is
for switching roommates.

1138
00:56:29.083 --> 00:56:30.708
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

1139
00:56:31.208 --> 00:56:33.957
Switching roommates is a last resort.

1140
00:56:33.958 --> 00:56:37.207
The school only allows that in extreme circumstances.

1141
00:56:37.208 --> 00:56:39.249
She'd have to be. like. threatening your life or…

1142
00:56:39.250 --> 00:56:42.665
I'm just… I'm having a problem with boundaries.

1143
00:56:42.666 --> 00:56:44.416
if you have any advice about that?

1144
00:56:44.916 --> 00:56:48.457
The thing about communication is
that you're not gonna get what you want

1145
00:56:48.458 --> 00:56:50.207
unless you ask for it.

1146
00:56:50.208 --> 00:56:51.666
So just be direct.

1147
00:56:54.333 --> 00:56:56.374
Celeste. can I talk to you about something?

1148
00:56:56.375 --> 00:56:58.624
Not now. After we watch <i>Clueless.</i>

1149
00:56:58.625 --> 00:57:03.332
Oh my God. I cannot believe
you haven't seen this fucking movie.

1150
00:57:03.333 --> 00:57:05.207
- You were so sheltered.
<i>- He gave me a C-minus.</i>

1151
00:57:05.208 --> 00:57:07.207
<i>- Well. he gave me a C…</i>
- Trivia fact.

1152
00:57:07.208 --> 00:57:10.000
Stacey Dash was 30 when she filmed this.

1153
00:57:10.500 --> 00:57:12.458
30? That's close to your age.

1154
00:57:16.416 --> 00:57:18.165
Whoa! What the fuck?

1155
00:57:18.166 --> 00:57:20.041
Sorry. I. um…

1156
00:57:20.541 --> 00:57:22.708
I just have to charge my computer.

1157
00:57:23.291 --> 00:57:24.833
It's about to die.

1158
00:57:27.166 --> 00:57:28.916
- Go back.
- Yeah.

1159
00:57:30.541 --> 00:57:32.415
<i>- Did you get your report card?
- Yeah.</i>

1160
00:57:32.416 --> 00:57:34.165
<i>I'm toast. How'd you do?</i>

1161
00:57:34.166 --> 00:57:37.541
<i>I totally choked. My father is gonna go ballistic on me.</i>

1162
00:57:38.625 --> 00:57:42.749
So I have really enjoyed
reading all your poems this semester.

1163
00:57:42.750 --> 00:57:46.582
I loved it so much that I think
the entire class should get a chance

1164
00:57:46.583 --> 00:57:48.124
to hear them before winter break.

1165
00:57:48.125 --> 00:57:50.790
Oh. come on. Who's gonna kick us off?

1166
00:57:50.791 --> 00:57:52.082
Anybody?

1167
00:57:52.083 --> 00:57:53.916
- Don't jump up at once.
- I'll go.

1168
00:57:54.625 --> 00:57:56.583
Celeste. all right. come on down.

1169
00:58:04.166 --> 00:58:05.791
My poem is called.

1170
00:58:06.583 --> 00:58:09.333
<i>The Girl Who's Barely There.</i>

1171
00:58:10.791 --> 00:58:12.125
<i>It's 8:00 a.m.</i>

1172
00:58:12.625 --> 00:58:16.207
<i>The girl methodically Puts together an outfit.</i>

1173
00:58:16.208 --> 00:58:19.291
<i>That precisely zero people will notice.</i>

1174
00:58:19.791 --> 00:58:21.125
<i>It's almost as if.</i>

1175
00:58:22.083 --> 00:58:23.083
<i>That's her goal.</i>

1176
00:58:23.541 --> 00:58:26.040
<i>To be imperceptible.</i>

1177
00:58:26.041 --> 00:58:27.957
<i>Inoffensive.</i>

1178
00:58:27.958 --> 00:58:30.208
<i>Insignificant.</i>

1179
00:58:30.708 --> 00:58:33.750
<i>She's the girl who's barely there.</i>

1180
00:58:34.916 --> 00:58:36.332
<i>It's noon.</i>

1181
00:58:36.333 --> 00:58:41.207
<i>The girl laughs too hard At a joke of a handsome senior.</i>

1182
00:58:41.208 --> 00:58:43.082
<i>He's a kaleidoscope.</i>

1183
00:58:43.083 --> 00:58:44.708
<i>She's beige.</i>

1184
00:58:45.291 --> 00:58:47.500
<i>Yet also clear.</i>

1185
00:58:48.416 --> 00:58:51.791
<i>She's the girl who's barely there.</i>

1186
00:58:52.291 --> 00:58:53.582
<i>It's 10:00 p.m.</i>

1187
00:58:53.583 --> 00:58:56.207
<i>The girl waits for someone To make plans for her.</i>

1188
00:58:56.208 --> 00:58:57.624
<i>She wonders.</i>

1189
00:58:57.625 --> 00:59:02.249
<i>"Do I exist merely to refract The brilliance of others?"</i>

1190
00:59:02.250 --> 00:59:04.957
<i>"Am I like a glass wall.</i>

1191
00:59:04.958 --> 00:59:09.625
<i>So translucent that someone
Might walk straight through me?"</i>

1192
00:59:10.666 --> 00:59:13.625
<i>Crash. sweep. trash.</i>

1193
00:59:14.125 --> 00:59:15.125
<i>Gone.</i>

1194
00:59:15.958 --> 00:59:20.083
<i>She's the girl who used to be there.</i>

1195
00:59:27.750 --> 00:59:29.957
Great job. Celeste.

1196
00:59:29.958 --> 00:59:33.332
Oh. I love your use of imagery
and how you played with form.

1197
00:59:33.333 --> 00:59:36.582
All right. uh. let's open it up.
What else did people notice?

1198
00:59:36.583 --> 00:59:37.583
Mara?

1199
00:59:38.625 --> 00:59:45.166
Celeste did a great job of capturing
the emptiness of the character.

1200
00:59:45.666 --> 00:59:47.999
We all know this girl.

1201
00:59:48.000 --> 00:59:51.915
and you just wanna go up to her
and say. "You're not the victim."

1202
00:59:51.916 --> 00:59:53.375
"You just suck."

1203
00:59:55.000 --> 00:59:57.333
I see you've met my ex.

1204
00:59:58.208 --> 01:00:00.833
That was inappropriate. Anyone else?

1205
01:00:02.375 --> 01:00:03.458
Theo?

1206
01:00:04.416 --> 01:00:06.625
Um. I thought we had to rhyme.

1207
01:00:07.791 --> 01:00:11.249
You're not supposed to rhyme.
okay? Not every poem is a rhyme.

1208
01:00:11.250 --> 01:00:13.915
If you ever wrote a poem
about me like that. I'd fuckin' kill you.

1209
01:00:13.916 --> 01:00:15.165
Well. you did that already.

1210
01:00:15.166 --> 01:00:17.665
Remember when you sang that song at open mic night

1211
